{
  "texts": [
    "As it is shown in Fig. 15, RankSVM model is applied over the essay representation to identify essays with low scores and high scores for negative and positive samples to be used in the next stage.",
    "In the second stage (prompt-dependent stage), the main objective is to capture semantic, part-of-speech, and syntactic information.",
    "To capture the semantic and the part-of-speech information, the essay is represented using a hierarchical document structure, with word vectors are grouped into sentences, and then sentences are grouped into essays.",
    "On the other hand, to capture the syntactic information, essays are transformed into phrases, then sentences, and finally into a complete essay.",
    "At each level of the hierarchy, Bi-LSTM is employed to capture contextual dependency."
  ]
}